  "prompt": "What is the best phone under 12k currently?",
  "response": "As of the latest data in October 2023, the best phone under 12k INR can vary based on personal preferences and needs such as camera quality, battery life, performance, and brand preference. However, here are some of the top contenders you might consider:\n\n1. **Realme Narzo 50A**:\n   - Display: 6.5-inch HD+ IPS LCD\n   - Processor: MediaTek Helio G85\n   - Camera: Triple camera setup (50MP main sensor)\n   - Battery: 6000mAh\n\n2. **Redmi 10 Prime**:\n   - Display: 6.5-inch FHD+ IPS LCD\n   - Processor: MediaTek Helio G88\n   - Camera: Quad camera setup (50MP main sensor)\n   - Battery: 6000mAh\n\n3. **Samsung Galaxy M12**:\n   - Display: 6.5-inch HD+ PLS IPS\n   - Processor: Exynos 850\n   - Camera: Quad camera setup (48MP main sensor)\n   - Battery: 6000mAh\n\n4. **Poco M3**:\n   - Display: 6.53-inch FHD+ IPS LCD\n   - Processor: Qualcomm Snapdragon 662\n   - Camera: Triple camera setup (48MP main sensor)\n   - Battery: 6000mAh\n\n5. **Moto G31**:\n   - Display: 6.4-inch FHD+ AMOLED\n   - Processor: MediaTek Helio G85\n   - Camera: Triple camera setup (50MP main sensor)\n   - Battery: 5000mAh\n\nThese models offer a good balance of features and performance for their price. You may also want to check user reviews and ratings to see which phone suits your specific needs best. Additionally, it\u2019s always useful to check for recent launches or updates in models which might also fit your criteria.",
